The following traits were recorded on each genotype at Lincoln and Mead: days to heading (measured by calculating the number of days after Jan. 1 to when 50% of the tillers in each genotype were at Feekes stage 10.1 and had heads fully emerged from the boot), average chlorophyll content from five flag leaves (Feekes stage 10.5, measuring using SPAD-502 m (KONICA MINOLTA, New York, USA; [36]), and plant height (measured during ripening stage (Feekes stage 11) as the height of the plant from the ground to the tip of the head, awns excluded). In addition, common bunt resistance was measured on each genotype in each replication as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
